node.contents: It turns out that all those threads are Garbage Collection threads.

astNode.text: It turns out that all those threads are Garbage Collection threads.

node.contents: Our program generates very very large object and kept in memory.

astNode.text: Our program generates very very large object and kept in memory.

node.contents: When the heap running low, gc threads will do their works. And since all those objects are in old region, and none of them can be released, the threads keep running FGC.

astNode.text: When the heap running low, gc threads will do their works. And since all those objects are in old region, and none of them can be released, the threads keep running FGC.
